&lt;h1 class="relative group">Journey Of The Siddhartha
&lt;div id="journey-of-the-siddhartha" class="anchor">&lt;/div>
&lt;span
class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100">
&lt;a class="group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700"
style="text-decoration-line: none !important;" href="#journey-of-the-siddhartha" aria-label="Anchor">#&lt;/a>
&lt;/span>
&lt;/h1>
&lt;p>The world around us has mysterious ways, &lt;br>
to teach some deeper lessons of life. &lt;br>
In ancient time there was a Siddhartha &lt;br>
He was a prince and had all luxuries &lt;br>
At his disposal to enjoy the life &lt;br>
But, he saw suffering and Dukkha &lt;br>
In a certain way of living &lt;br>
and started a journey &lt;br>
to free from the clutches of Dukkha. &lt;br>
And he became The Siddhartha, The Buddha.&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>